                <p class="team-description">
                    Zakira Shyrose Jaffer Dhalla is a world-renowned Islamic lecturer with a bachelor’s degree in Psychology and Sociology and a master’s degree in Education. She is an Anti-racist Education Counsellor by profession and is a polyglot who travels internationally to spread the teachings and love of the Holy Prophet's family ﷺ, in English, Urdu and Gujarati. Shyrose successfully acquired the certificate in conflict management and mediation for faith leaders from the Canadian Collaborative for Engagement and Conflict Mangement, (CECM).
                    She is an award-winning speaker who holds the honor of being the only Muslim woman to have spoken not once but twice outside the White House in Washington DC. Shyrose is a published writer and magazine columnist and is a popular tv guest and a familiar face on a myriad of Islamic channels around the world. She hosts her own weekly tv programs on several tv channels in English and Urdu and is also a published playwright, a well-known humanitarian and a master fundraiser for charitable causes. She is also an accomplished latimiyya and nasheed reciter and a well-known social activist.
                    She is extremely well known for her puppet shows and has spoken at many Ivy League universities including Princeton University and is famous for her talks at large processions and juloos in Toronto, Stockholm, Leicester, Mumbai and other cities around the world.
                    Zakira Shyrose is married to a family Physician and has 3 children aged 25, 24 and 16 yrs.
                    Shyrose is looking forward to helping families and couples navigate conflict.
                </p>
